    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-10-29T18:23:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-10-29T18:23:00-05:00" n="285"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d285">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">353/10–2953: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d285fn1">Drafted by <persName>Jones</persName> (<gloss
                            target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss>) and concurred in by Deputy Assistant
                            Secretary<persName corresp="#p_SANDIFERDV1">Sandifer</persName>, cleared
                        with the Bureau of European Affairs and <gloss target="#t_LUNA1"
                            >L/UNA</gloss>, approved for transmission by <persName
                            corresp="#p_POPPERDH1">Popper</persName>, and signed by Assistant
                        Secretary <persName corresp="#p_MURPHYRD1">Murphy</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-10-29T18:23:00-05:00"
                            >October 29, 1953—6:23 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss> 48. Re <gloss target="#t_ICJ1"
                        >ICJ</gloss> election. While you should not campaign against election of
                        <persName>Kozhevnikov</persName>, who we assume will receive widest support
                    in view sentiment in favor election of judges of Big Five to <gloss
                        target="#t_ICJ1">ICJ</gloss>, you should not vote for him in <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> or <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> but should
                    abstain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
